&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Telesales Agent - Automotive - English and German language&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Infomedia &amp;amp; the role&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Infomedia is a leading global provider of SaaS solutions to the parts and service sector of the automotive industry. Headquartered in Australia, Infomedia has been at the forefront of aftersales system innovation for more than 28 years. Supplying online parts selling systems, sophisticated service selling systems, a range of publications, as well as data analysis and information research for automotive and lubricant industries. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our software solutions are used each business day by over 220,000 dealership personnel, produced in more than 35 languages and at work in 186 countries. Their powerful search functions and intuitive, user-friendly interface helps boost efficiency, profitability and customer retention for OE Parts and Service Departments.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Telesales Agent you will play a key part in generating and qualifying leads, scheduling appointments, and ensuring accurate CRM data. You will work closely with both Marketing and Sales to ensure a strong, well-managed pipeline of new business opportunities. Written and verbal business English and German language skills are required. You will also support the Senior Business Developer in different markets and be part of the Sales Team in EMEA Region.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours of work and location&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our team works Monday – Friday, either 7.00am – 4.00pm or 8.00am – 5.00pm.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would require the candidate to occasionally work outside of office hours, primarily to communicate with colleagues in Australia and the US. Ability to travel within the EMEA region periodically.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, research, and qualify leads in collaboration with marketing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct cold calls and outbound outreach to engage new prospects and follow up with existing customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and pre-qualify leads via phone and email before passing them to the Business Development Managers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Source and research potential clients using LinkedIn, Cognism, and other tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide ongoing updates on sales performance and business development activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the sales team with information requests, pricing, and contract preparation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with marketing campaigns, including pulling email lists from Salesforce and supporting bulk mailouts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage Salesforce data to ensure all lead, opportunity, and customer information is accurate and up to date&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide administrative support to the Head of Region and contribute to wider sales initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a positive representative of Infomedia and uphold high standards of professionalism and integrity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
